'''Iskalonian''' was the general term for seventeen different [[Water/Legends|aquatic]] [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Species/Legends|species]] who lived in the [[Ocean/Legends|oceans]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Iskalon/Legends|Iskalon]]. At least six of these species were relocated from their own [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworlds]] to Iskalon circa [[5000 BBY/Legends|5000 BBY]].

==Biology and appearance==
The six main species in [[the School]] were the [[Inleshat/Legends|Inleshat]], [[Chuhkyvi]], [[Striber]]s, [[Graygl]], [[Nejma]], and the [[Frid]].

Among the other species represented in the School was that of a [[Gender/Legends|female]] Iskalonian named [[Dania Francis]]. [[Dania Francis's species]] had a humanoid torso, a [[Horse/Legends|horse]]-like face, a [[Fish/Legends|fish]]-like lower body featuring a finless tail carried curled forward, wing-like fins attached to her shoulders, and additional fins running the length of her lower body. Francis also had purple skin, white hair, and white eyes.<ref name="Star Wars 102">[[Star Wars (1977) 102|''Star Wars'' (1977) 102]]</ref>

Another Iskalonian of a species had a fish-like appearance (distinct from that of a Frid), green skin, large white eyes with thick eyelids, and a fin on his or her head which formed a spiny crest. This Iskalonian had a face resembling a [[Dog/Legends|dog's]] muzzle.<ref name="Star Wars 74">[[Star Wars (1977) 74|''Star Wars'' (1977) 74]]</ref>

==History==
Around five hundred years before the [[Battle of Naboo/Legends|Battle of Naboo]], a number of needy Iskalonian locals were approached by recruiters sent by [[Hugo Bartyn]]. Bartyn wanted amphibian fishermen to settle a new city in [[Lamaredd/Legends|Lamaredd]] and tempted these poverty-stricken individuals with promises of untouched seas in a new frontier. Once they arrived, however, they became [[Slavery/Legends|slave]] laborers. Most of the Iskalonians refused, and they were banished to an almost-sure death in the open seas.<ref name="BL">{{GamerCite|7|Bartyn's Landing (article)}}</ref>

Though they built the underwater city of [[Pavillion]] to interact with water-breathing visitors to Iskalon, it was destroyed in [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]] after an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] attack set off an enormous tidal wave. Afterwards, the Iskalonians withdrew from [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] affairs. [[Kiro]] was an exception to this, as he briefly left his homeworld for several adventures alongside [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]].

==Iskalonians in the galaxy==
The Iskalonians continued their isolationist ways, even after a brief invasion by the [[Nagai/Legends|Nagai]] was driven off (thanks to Kiro and Skywalker). The Iskalonians did not join the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]].

